UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Railroad Australia
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Documentary series. Pacific National's Steel Train battles the Nullarbor to deliver its vital cargo across Australia, and a broken loco gets master mechanic Mick steaming. S2 Ep10

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Border Force America's Gatekeepers

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Aussie Road Train Truckers

UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Rick takes a trip back in time to his early days running a nightclub in Padstow before making the ultimate fish pie with some deliciously plump pollock. S2 Ep1

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Would I Lie To You?

E4Plus1.uk.description: A Patch, a Modem, and a Zantac: Sheldon is determined to be proved right when a NASA official comes to school and dismisses one of his scientific suggestions. (S1 Ep6/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Fabulous Faker Boy: Bart doesn't want to go to piano lessons, until he meets his beautiful teacher... Homer loses the last two hairs on his head. (S24 Ep20/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Saga of Carl: Homer, Moe, Lenny and Carl win the lottery, but Carl runs off to Iceland with the winnings. (S24 Ep21/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Electric Can Opener Fluctuation: Leonard's attempts to woo Penny are constantly thwarted. Sheldon heads to Texas after learning his friends meddled with his expedition data. (S3 Ep1)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Jiminy Conjecture: Leonard and Penny feel awkward around each other after their romantic liaison, while Sheldon and Howard take bets to determine a species of cricket. (S3 Ep2)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Gothowitz Deviation: Sheldon tries to modify Penny's behaviour, and rewards her with chocolate when she does what he wants, while Howard and Raj go to a goth nightclub. (S3 Ep3)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Pirate Solution: Raj must find a job or he'll be sent back to India, so he accepts an offer of work from Sheldon. Leonard and Penny try to get some time for themselves. (S3 Ep4)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Front: At his high school reunion, Homer wins several awards including 'Most Weight Gained' and 'Most Improved Odour'. But then the Principal finds out he never graduated. (S4 Ep19/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Whacking Day: Lisa asks singer Barry White to help stop the cruel Springfield 'Whacking Day' tradition of hitting snakes with sticks. (S4 Ep20/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Hollyoaks
E4Plus1.uk.description: Tony begins his physio sessions with Mercedes' support. Meanwhile, with the truth now revealed, tension rises between two residents.

E4Plus1.uk.title: New: Animal Control
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series - Tortoises and Labradors: US sitcom. Frank unearths an illegal animal smuggling ring. Shred's first night shift introduces him to the world of furry parties. (S2 Ep3/9)

E4Plus1.uk.title: America's Next Top Model
E4Plus1.uk.description: Erin Wasson: Series 16 of Tyra Banks' iconic reality series begins with a brutal switcheroo and a catwalk across a watery runway inside giant plastic bubbles. (S16 Ep1)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: Britain's sharpest armchair critics have been watching: Starstruck, The Home Edit, Made in Chelsea, SAS, This Is Going to Hurt, Dynasties II, and Pam & Tommy. (S19 Ep16)

E4Plus1.uk.title: First Dates
E4Plus1.uk.description: Will trainee astronaut Nicky's date with motoring journalist Daniel be out of this world? Road sweeper Bruce, who's 58, is looking for a lady who'll love him for who he is. (S8 Ep9)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Naked Attraction
E4Plus1.uk.description: A celebration of Naked Attraction's very best naughty bits, revisiting times when the pickers got it spot on and chose their perfect date, including Gemma and James who found love.

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Holographic Excitation: The gang celebrate Halloween with a fancy dress party at Stuart's comic book shop, but Sheldon and Amy can't agree on which costumes to wear. (S6 Ep5)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Extract Obliteration: Sheldon is thrilled when Stephen Hawking agrees to play against him in an online game. Penny signs up for a class at the community college. (S6 Ep6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: Britain's sharpest armchair critics have been watching: Starstruck, The Home Edit, Made in Chelsea, SAS, This Is Going to Hurt, Dynasties II, and Pam & Tommy. (S19 Ep16) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: Yanni's: Gordon Ramsay visits Greek restaurant Yanni's, where he clashes with owner Peter, a chef who hasn't changed his menu since the business opened in 1984. (S6 Ep10) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Last Exit to Springfield: Homer takes on Mr Burns in a labour struggle that rapidly spirals out of control after Homer leads the workers on strike. (S4 Ep17/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Young Sheldon
E4Plus1.uk.description: A Solar Calculator, a Game Ball, and a Cheerleader's Bosom: Sheldon struggles with his new-found popularity after he uses statistics to help the school football team. (S1 Ep5/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Young Sheldon
E4Plus1.uk.description: A Patch, a Modem, and a Zantac: Sheldon is determined to be proved right when a NASA official comes to school and dismisses one of his scientific suggestions. (S1 Ep6/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Good Grief: It's another epic Halloween full of costumes, tricks and treats for the Dunphy-Pritchett-Tucker clan as they deal with huge, unexpected news. (S10 Ep5)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Neighborhood
E4Plus1.uk.description: Welcome to the Test Run: Gemma wants another baby, but Dave's worried that she's forgotten how difficult caring for a new-born is, so he gets a robotic doll to remind her. (S3 Ep16)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Neighborhood
E4Plus1.uk.description: Welcome to the Invasion: When Calvin's arch-rivals, the Pink Ladies, move their manicure business into the local barbershop, Dave encourages him to make peace. (S3 Ep17)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Neighborhood
E4Plus1.uk.description: Welcome to the Surprise: Calvin receives an unconventional birthday gift involving his dad, so Dave suggests they spend the day celebrating the late patriarch. (S3 Ep18)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Dear Beloved Family: Gloria rushes Phil to hospital for emergency surgery when he experiences intense stomach pains. (S9 Ep12)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: In Your Head: Luke goes missing after a night out. Can Manny, Phil and Gloria find him? Haley tries to land an interview with the creator of a big lifestyle website. (S9 Ep13)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Rude(ish) Tube Shorts
E4Plus1.uk.description: A short, cheeky clip from Rude Tube's naughty little sister, Rude(ish) Tube, featuring sports of the lawnmower, motorbike and bicycle variety.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: Return to Amy's Baking Company: Gordon revisits the most contentious restaurant he's ever tried to rescue - Amy's Baking Company, in Scottsdale, Arizona. (S7 Ep10) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: Pantaleone's: In Colorado, Gordon visits Italian restaurant Pantaleone's, whose stubborn owner Pete claims that he makes 'the best pizza in Denver'. Sadly, Gordon doesn't agree. (S7 Ep1) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: A Test Before Trying: When the school's threatened with closure because of low test scores, its fate rests with one student who missed the exam: Bart. (S24 Ep10/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Changing of the Guardian: After surviving a tornado, Marge and Homer seek out guardians for the kids, in case the worst should ever happen to them. (S24 Ep11/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Valentino Submergence: Sheldon and Amy host a special live Valentine's Day episode of their internet show Fun with Flags. Leonard and Penny grapple with getting older. (S9 Ep15)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Positive Negative Reaction: When Bernadette makes a big announcement, Howard becomes convinced that he needs to start earning more money. (S9 Ep16)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Other People's Children: It's male-bonding day when Jay takes Luke into the garage to show him how to use tools and impart some manly wisdom. (S5 Ep17)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Vegas: The adults are Vegas-bound when Jay hooks them up with Excelsior Level hotel accommodation, courtesy of one of his big clients. (S5 Ep18)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Panty Piata Polarization: Sheldon bans Penny from the flat for numerous minor infractions, so she retaliates. Howard and Raj search for the America's Next Top Model house. (S2 Ep7)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Lizard-Spock Expansion: Howard is furious when a woman who he likes falls for Leonard, despite Howard's efforts to woo her. (S2 Ep8)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The White Asparagus Triangulation: Sheldon is delighted that Leonard has finally found a girlfriend who matches up to his high standards... Perhaps a little too delighted. (S2 Ep9)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Vartabedian Conundrum: Leonard goes to Penny for help when his relationship with Stephanie takes off faster than he'd like, but will he act on her advice? (S2 Ep10)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Young Sheldon
E4Plus1.uk.description: A Brisket, Voodoo, and Cannonball Run: The kids try to suggest ways to resolve a family feud when Meemaw refuses to give George Sr her secret brisket recipe. (S1 Ep7/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Young Sheldon
E4Plus1.uk.description: Cape Canaveral, Schrdinger's Cat, and Cyndi Lauper's Hair: In an attempt to bond with Sheldon, George Sr takes the boys on a trip to see the space shuttle launch. (S1 Ep8/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Dangers on a Train: While she's browsing for wedding anniversary cakes, Marge stumbles across a website for married people who want to have affairs. (S24 Ep22/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Heartbreak Hotel: Homer and Marge go on a big reality TV competition but are eliminated immediately. And the blame game starts soon after... (S30 Ep2/23)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Creepy Candy Coating Corollary: Due to a childhood snub, Sheldon is irked when Star Trek actor Wil Wheaton (guest starring as himself) takes part in the same contest as him. (S3 Ep5)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Cornhusker Vortex: Sheldon teaches Leonard about American football so that he can try to fit in with Penny's friends. And Raj and Sheldon have a kite-fighting contest. (S3 Ep6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Guitarist Amplification: Sheldon is annoyed when Leonard and Penny argue about Penny's male friend staying over and he has to act as peacemaker. (S3 Ep7)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Adhesive Duck Deficiency: Leonard, Raj and Howard go on a camping trip that alters their minds. Penny dislocates her shoulder when she slips in the shower. (S3 Ep8)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Krusty Gets Cancelled: When Krusty's show gets axed, Bart and Lisa enlist Bette Midler, Hugh Hefner, the Red Hot Chili Peppers and Elizabeth Taylor to help him get it back. (S4 Ep22/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Homer's Barbershop Quartet: Homer reminisces about the Be Sharps, the barbershop quartet he was in with Barney, Apu and Principal Skinner. Guest starring George Harrison. (S5 Ep1/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Peeping Mom: Bart lies to cover up his role in a bulldozer crash, so Marge decides to follow him everywhere until he confesses. Ned's cute new dog loves Homer. (S26 Ep18/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: New: Animal Control
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series - Big Dogs and Mini Horses: US sitcom. Frank's frustrated when Emily, who's a stickler for rules, accompanies him on a call. Shred and Patel throw a party. (S2 Ep4/9)

E4Plus1.uk.title: America's Next Top Model
E4Plus1.uk.description: Alek Wek: A foul fowl fracas ensues when two of the models find a plate of rotten chicken. And there's a sting in the tail at the photo shoot, where they work with live bees... (S16 Ep2)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: Britain's sharpest armchair critics watch The Masked Dancer, Married at First Sight UK, Nadiya's Everyday Baking, Bad Sisters and This Is MY House. (S20 Ep1)

E4Plus1.uk.title: First Dates
E4Plus1.uk.description: Dad-of-two Graeme, who's 33 and six foot five, is on his first date since he sadly lost his wife. Rock fan Anthony, who's 64, meets retired nurse and amateur magician Barbara. (S8 Ep11)

Film4.uk.title: Vesper
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Sci-fi fantasy with new-comer Raffiella Chapman and Eddie Marsan. A resourceful teenager scavenges to survive in a mushy and mushroom-y post-apocalyptic world of have and have-nots.

Film4.uk.title: 3:10 to Yuma
Film4.uk.description: (2007) Western starring Christian Bale and Russell Crowe. An impoverished rancher tries to earn some money and his family's respect by escorting a dangerous outlaw on his way to jail.

Film4.uk.title: Amanda
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Mikhael Hers's quietly sensitive drama. A young man becomes responsible for raising his seven-year-old niece after his sister is killed in a Paris terrorist attack. In French/subs.

Film4.uk.title: Young Winston
Film4.uk.description: (1972) Biopic charting the rise of the future PM from battered Harrow pupil to MP via military action on foreign soil. Directed by Richard Attenborough.

Film4.uk.title: Time Lock
Film4.uk.description: (1957) Gripping drama with Robert Beatty. An expert team races against the clock to save a six-year-old boy who's been trapped in a seemingly impregnable bank vault.

Film4.uk.title: Patton
Film4.uk.description: (1970) Multi-Oscar-winning, fact-based, Second World War drama starring George C Scott, who gives a vivid portrait of the famously straight-talking US commander General George Patton.

Film4.uk.title: Instant Family
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Comedy. Mark Wahlberg and Rose Byrne star as a couple whose orderly lives are disrupted when they foster three kids. Based on director Sean Anders' own experience.

Film4.uk.title: The Artifice Girl
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Franklin Ritch's strikingly claustrophobic AI thriller. A man creates a virtual nine-year-old to lure online predators from the shadows. But as she learns, she becomes more real...

Film4.uk.title: Alita: Battle Angel
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Partially animated action film based on a popular manga comic. Alita, a deadly cyborg brought back to life by a mourning scientist, sets out to discover her true identity.

Film4.uk.title: Hilary and Jackie
Film4.uk.description: (1999) Fact-based drama about the lives of the troubled genius, cellist Jacqueline du Pr (Emily Watson) and her sister Hilary (Rachel Griffiths). With David Morrissey. Strong language.

Film4.uk.title: Two Way Stretch
Film4.uk.description: (1960) Comedy. Peter Sellers, Bernard Cribbins and David Lodge star as criminals happily incarcerated in a prison run like a home-from-home for old lags and rascals by a liberal governor.

Film4.uk.title: A Kid for Two Farthings
Film4.uk.description: (1955) Carol Reed's charming film stars Jonathan Ashmore as a young, impressionable boy who mistakes a one-horned goat for a unicorn in London's colourful Petticoat Lane market.

Film4.uk.title: Nothing But the Best
Film4.uk.description: (1964) Classic British dark comedy with Alan Bates and Denholm Elliott. An ambitious estate agent's clerk hires a toff to teach him to be posh. Couldn't possibly lead to murder, could it?

Film4.uk.title: The Sheriff of Fractured Jaw
Film4.uk.description: (1959) Comedy western with Kenneth More. An English gunsmith decides the Wild West is the best market for his wares, but little does he expect to end up sheriff of a lawless frontier town.

Film4.uk.title: Steel Magnolias
Film4.uk.description: (1989) Star-studded tragi-comedy with Julia Roberts, Daryl Hannah, Dolly Parton and more. Six Southern belles console and cajole each other through life in a Louisiana beauty parlour.

Film4.uk.title: Moon
Film4.uk.description: (2009) Psychological sci-fi thriller. Sam Rockwell stars as a man who lives alone on the moon overseeing a mining operation. His time's nearly done, but he's started to go a bit peculiar...

Film4.uk.title: Darkman
Film4.uk.description: (1990) Liam Neeson and Frances McDormand star in Sam Raimi's crime-fighting action-fantasy. A scientist uses his invention to seek revenge on his attackers.

Film4.uk.title: Blade of the Immortal
Film4.uk.description: (2017) Action adventure. Legendary director Takashi Miike's 100th film stars Takuya Kimura as an immortal samurai hired by a young woman to avenge her father's murder. In Japanese/subs.

Film4.uk.title: The Blue Lamp

Film4.uk.title: The Swimmer
Film4.uk.description: (1968) Burt Lancaster stars as the angst-ridden middle-aged man who decides to swim home via neighbour's pools in Frank and Eleanor Perry's superb allegorical drama.

Film4.uk.title: All the King's Men
